get.description:
Stream search results using Server-Sent Events (SSE).

This endpoint streams search results as they become available,
providing real-time updates to the client.

Event types:
- `start`: Search initiated (contains query metadata)
- `result`: Individual search result
- `progress`: Progress update (every 5 results)
- `complete`: Search finished (contains summary)
- `error`: Error occurred

Example client code (JavaScript):
```javascript
const eventSource = new EventSource('/v1/stream/search?q=python');
eventSource.addEventListener('result', (e) => {
    const result = JSON.parse(e.data);
    console.log(result.title, result.url);
});
eventSource.addEventListener('complete', (e) => {
    const summary = JSON.parse(e.data);
    console.log('Done:', summary.total_results, 'results');
    eventSource.close();
});
eventSource.addEventListener('error', (e) => {
    console.error('Search error:', e.data);
    eventSource.close();
});
```
